<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Http_Request::setRequestUri() doesn't parses query strings as PHP does, if parameter names contain square brackets [] and/or other separators than ampersands &amp;. 
i.e.:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
?foo[]=bar;foo[]=baz
</code></pre>

<p>PHP's function parse_str() neither ignores []s nor arg_separator.input.</p>

<p>The URI is currently parsed using string functions, but this could be done using parse_url().</p>

